Using the textbooks table, make a list of all of the textbooks. Include the subject, the current book title, and the out of date book title. Order the results by the current textbook title.
SELECT A.Subject
, A.Title AS textbook
, B.Title AS previous_version
FROM Textbooks A
LEFT JOIN Textbooks B
ON A.TextbookID = B.UpdatedVersion
ORDER BY textbook;


List of all the textbooks that have an updated version.
SELECT A.Subject
, A.Title AS textbook
, B.Title AS previous_version
FROM Textbooks A
INNER JOIN Textbooks B
ON A.TextbookID = B.UpdatedVersion
ORDER BY textbook;


Using the authors table, make a list of all the authors who are reviewing a book.
SELECT authors.AuthorID
, authors.Name as Reviewer
, peers.Name as Being_reviewed
FROM Authors authors
INNER JOIN Authors peers
ON authors.reviewing = peers.authorID
ORDER BY authors.AuthorID

